08/11/2006
VIENNA, Austria -- Chancellor Wolfgang Schuessel met with Macedonian Prime Minister Nikola Gruevski on Tuesday (November 7th), on the sidelines of the Third Vienna Economic Forum. Schuessel reiterated Austria's support for Macedonia's Euro-Atlantic bid. Both leaders agreed that resolving Kosovo's status is crucial to regional security. 
Also in Vienna, Gruevski met with BiH counterpart Adnan Terzic. They reportedly agreed that BiH would supply Macedonia with electricity, should the country face blackouts over the winter. (MIA, Makfax - 07/11/06)
